reviews.text: Sunnyside is an amazing park, I was there for the Coca Cola Classic Disc Golf Tournament. Awesome weekend.
Loved the park with the rolling hills and trees. Had a wonderful firepit and frisbee golf
Nice relaxing place to picnic or just chill and listen to nature.
Nice quiet place to camp without the noise. Secluded and safe
Nice playground equipment, lots of shade trees, not much traffic. Nice place to have a picnic and play.

Havana belongs on any foodie's "Note to Self" page during visits to Bar Harbor.  Innovative menu for vegans and meat-lovers alike (rare!) and an inviting wine list to boot.  That they remain open most of the year - even off season - adds to our delight in visiting.  Love this place.
Really lovely little restaurant with a friendly staff.  The food was very good and the beer selection decent.  Although they got both of my beer orders wrong I would definitely go back.

Excellent restaurant. Had the fish of the day and by far was the best fish I've ever had. Portion is a little small and wait times can be long, but it is what it is. A few other patrons had the tapas and they looked excellent as well. Would recommend.

Our experience at Havana is second to none. The service was incredible matched only by the food and drinks. Enrique our server was fantastic. I highly recommend the black bean soup, the empanadas and the farmhouse salad, and the Havana martini is tasty.  Thanks!!

Best paella I've ever eaten - generous helping of perfectly-cooked seafood and the saucy rice was just spot on. But everything we had was delicious anyway. The mashed potatoes with coconut that came with one of the daily specials was just... So good...

The wine list is nuts, apparently one of the largest in the region. They have the little notes in the wine menu to help you choose, and we were really happy with the bottle we had.

And of course, the service was excellent. They open at 5pm but it appears that the live music starts a little later.

The history of this place is unbelievable. I was in complete awe the entire time. The architecture is gorgeous. This was a stop on the freedom trail and I couldn't be happier about it. Everyone is very knowledgeable and I was so pleased with my visit.
Went to Ruth Crisp Steakhouse. With my wife and friends. Everything was great.
So cool!!!!! And the best part were the martinis at Ruth Chris Steak House which is in the lobby of the OLD city hall.
Visited this wonderful historic building ,I was there for dinner at ruth chris's located inside

Visiting Boston is a delight. The red line tour is an excellent way for tourists to get to know history on their own.

Throughout the pavement, a brick line allows visitors to follow a map that guides -self-guided- tours of important historical buildings / monuments.

Here we found the Democratic symbol, the donkey and the explanation of the difference between it and the Republican, the elephant.

Don't miss the opportunity to visit Boston, follow the red line tour and learn about a City filled with history. The building at Boston's Old City Hall is exquisite.
Very detailed history...
Its a nice museum

Müze fazla büyük olmamasına rağmen içinde bulunan eserler günümüzden 4000 yıl öncesine kadar dayanıyor. Tamamına yakını bölgeden çıkarılan ve Edirne'nin tarihte ilkçağdan günümüze zamanda yolculuk gibi. Açık hava müzesi kısmında ilk anıt mezar örnekleri bulunmakta. Müze kartla veya küçük bir ücretle giriş mümkün Selimiye Camii'ne ve İslam Sanatları müzesine yakınlığıyla kısa sürede 3 güzel yeri gezme ve görme imkanına sahipsiniz. Ortalama 30-45 dk gibi bir süre yeterli olur bu müzeyi gezmeniz için. Edirne gezinize buradan başlamanızı tavsiye ederim .  Böylece tarihsel olarak gelişim ve değişimi görmeniz mümkün olacaktır.

Edirnenin en güzel yerlerinden biri. edirnenin kültür ve sanatını tarihin derinliklerinde sergileyen bir müze. ben çok beğeniyorum..gezilmesini tavsiye ediyorum. ayrıca mekan çok temiz . personel güler yüzlü ve nazik.

Edirne müze binası dışında bahçe alanına yapılmış. Tam bir açık hava müzesi. Aslında yağmur kar gibi etkilerden korunaklı olabilseydi daha iyi olurdu. Ayrıca bazı kalıntıların geçmişi ile ilgili bilgiler bulunmamakta. Gidin görün gezin. Çok büyük emeklerin sonucu bir araya getirilip yapılmış. Ellerine sağlık.
Perfect. Historical.

Balıkesir Saat Kulesi - Balıkesir

Saat Kulesi 1829 yılında Girit’li Mehmet Paşa tarafından İstanbul Galata Kulesi’nin benzeri olarak silindir şeklinde yaptırılmış idi. 1897 yılındaki deprem nedeniyle yıkılınca, 1901 yılında bugünkü şekliyle yeniden yaptırılmıştır. Kare prizma şeklindeki bina, beyaz kesme taş ile yapılmış ve kabartma işçiliklerle de süslü hale getirilmiştir.En üst kat kubbe ile örtülmüş ve büyük bir çan eklenmiştir. Buranın hemen altındaki katta ise dört yöne de birer saat konmuştur.

Bu kadar değerli bir eserin bu kadar biçimsiz bir noktada kalması kötü olmuş. Kuleyi yapanlar ileriyi görememişler. Kilise çanı benzeri her saat başı çalması müslüman mahallesinde salyangoza benziyor bu ses değişmeli
Şehire ayrı bir hava katan mimari yapı. Ne zaman çan başlasa içimden pink floyd high hopes mırıldanmama sebep oluyor..o nedenle ayrı seviyorum.
Kültürel mirasımızın emanet ettiği güzel yapılardan birisi

Do not miss the Museum of Contemporary Art in Bangkok! Not only is it a wonderful museum it is also a stunning piece of modern architecture. You'll need all day and then some more, a dream for any art buff there's five floors of spectacular exhibits. On the ground floor there's a restaurant, garden and an interactive experience. Take the family.  I loved it and next time I'm in Bangkok I'll be heading back for another look.👍🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

The Museum of Contemporary Art is from 2012. It is a private museum housed in a large building. 

There is no double pricing. Same price for a Thai and a foreigner. If you  are more than 60, you can enter for free. Not only Thais, but also foreigners. The price for a regular ticket is TB 250.

Obviously, most of the items on display in this museum are from Thailand, but on the fifth floor there is an interesting collection of foreign items.

Next to all items on display is a label with information in Thai and in English. 

You are allowed to use a camera inside the museum, but you cannot use a flash. There is one exception: you are not allowed to take pictures inside the special Robert Green collection on the fifth floor.

There is a coffee shop on the ground floor. There is a car park in the basement. 

The staff are friendly and helpful.

If you are interested in contemporary art, this place is definitely worth a visit.

Oh....
This is an ....hard to say.
They declare that this is a contemporary museum but this museum does not explore the comprehensive contemporary art all over the world because it’s simply this is a private museum owned by one business man.the collection is rely on his taste.of course this museum is playing a key role for collecting national artists of Thailand but mainly the collection is reflected on his preference.
I really love this spot because I can enjoy the most sophisticated art works in Bangkok.
I’ll come back here again.

Great museum. 
Beautiful building. Lots of great surrealism and some traditional Thai art. 
Definitely worth going although it's hard to get to, since the nearby train is not operational yet. Try to make sure your cab driver knows the place. Took us some time to get there but was worth it 👍👍

Surprisingly beautiful (and modern) structure that houses mostly modern and some traditional art. Peacefully quiet—not many locals seem aware it exists. The art is fascinating—a modern reinterpreting traditional Thai aesthetic forms. Lovely reprieve from the hot chaos of the city.
